- (5)  Finally,  mention  needs  to  be  made  of  the  thousands  of  products  in  Japan that  use  English  names, or  English-derived  names. Many of these  are  taken from  items  directly  imported  from  America.  However,  a very large  number of  these  product  names  are  created  in Japan.  The  Sony  WALKMAN -  one Japanese  name  that  became  popular  overseas  -  is but  one  example.

