English  loanwords  can  be  used  to  offer  potential  buyers  certain  food  genres or  items  in  reconstituted  forms.  This  is especially  prevalent  in  the  repackaging (i.e.,  the ' r e - p r e s e n t a t i o n ' ) of  some  traditional Japanese  snacks  like o-sembei ('rice  crackers').  For  example,  the  package  of Nice  Ecomomy  Ikappe ('Nice Economy  Potato  Crackers')  tells us  that  this  snack  is  ' reasonable price and quality goods'. Thus,  this  traditional  snack  has  now  become  a  good  buy  and  wise shopping  choice.

